                    redressal mechanism in higher education institutions facilitates the main constituents of the
                    institute including students, parents, teachers and other non-teaching staff to lodge grievances
                    and ensure satisfactory solutions in a hassle-free manner. Effective and timely redressal or
                    settlement of the grievances makes grievance redressal system mandatory in higher education
                    institution, according to the Ministry of Human Resource Development (MHRD), Government of
                    India..
                </p>
